{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":743,"text":"We always hear that texting is a scourge."},{"time":3605,"text":"The idea is that texting spells the decline and fall"},{"time":8445,"text":"of any kind of serious literacy, or at least writing ability,"},{"time":11945,"text":"among young people in the United States"},{"time":14588,"text":"and now the whole world today."},{"time":16889,"text":"The fact of the matter is that it just isn't true,"},{"time":20393,"text":"and it's easy to think that it is true,"},{"time":22896,"text":"but in order to see it in another way,"},{"time":24795,"text":"in order to see that actually texting is a miraculous thing,"},{"time":28464,"text":"not just energetic, but a miraculous thing,"},{"time":31029,"text":"a kind of emergent complexity"},{"time":32776,"text":"that we're seeing happening right now,"},{"time":35237,"text":"we have to pull the camera back for a bit"},{"time":37543,"text":"and look at what language really is,"},{"time":40961,"text":"in which case, one thing that we see"},{"time":43034,"text":"is that texting is not writing at all."},{"time":47658,"text":"What do I mean by that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":49480,"text":"Basically, if we think about language,"},{"time":52036,"text":"language has existed for perhaps 150,000 years,"},{"time":55837,"text":"at least 80,000 years,"},{"time":57974,"text":"and what it arose as is speech. People talked."},{"time":62125,"text":"That's what we're probably genetically specified for."},{"time":65149,"text":"That's how we use language most."},{"time":67340,"text":"Writing is something that came along much later,"},{"time":70822,"text":"and as we saw in the last talk,"},{"time":72878,"text":"there's a little bit of controversy as to exactly when that happened,"},{"time":75546,"text":"but according to traditional estimates,"},{"time":77862,"text":"if humanity had existed for 24 hours,"},{"time":81384,"text":"then writing only came along at about 11:07 p.m."},{"time":86575,"text":"That's how much of a latterly thing writing is."},{"time":90220,"text":"So first there's speech, and then writing comes along"},{"time":93608,"text":"as a kind of artifice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":95370,"text":"Now don't get me wrong, writing has certain advantages."},{"time":99376,"text":"When you write, because it's a conscious process,"},{"time":101959,"text":"because you can look backwards,"},{"time":104097,"text":"you can do things with language that are much less likely"},{"time":106927,"text":"if you're just talking."},{"time":109391,"text":"For example, imagine a passage from Edward Gibbon's"},{"time":113292,"text":"\"The Decline and Fall of the Roman Empire:\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":117098,"text":"\"The whole engagement lasted above twelve hours,"},{"time":120349,"text":"till the graduate retreat of the Persians was changed"},{"time":122651,"text":"into a disorderly flight, of which the shameful example"},{"time":125424,"text":"was given by the principal leaders and the Surenas himself.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":128011,"text":"That's beautiful, but let's face it, nobody talks that way."},{"time":132330,"text":"Or at least, they shouldn't if they're interested"},{"time":136566,"text":"in reproducing. That --"},{"time":139080,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":141799,"text":"is not the way any human being speaks casually."}]},{"cues":[{"time":144777,"text":"Casual speech is something quite different."},{"time":147362,"text":"Linguists have actually shown"},{"time":149218,"text":"that when we're speaking casually in an unmonitored way,"},{"time":151929,"text":"we tend to speak in word packets of maybe"},{"time":154607,"text":"seven to 10 words."},{"time":156417,"text":"You'll notice this if you ever have occasion to record"},{"time":159096,"text":"yourself or a group of people talking."},{"time":162089,"text":"That's what speech is like."},{"time":163544,"text":"Speech is much looser. It's much more telegraphic."},{"time":167849,"text":"It's much less reflective -- very different from writing."},{"time":171539,"text":"So we naturally tend to think, because we see language"},{"time":174475,"text":"written so often, that that's what language is,"},{"time":176917,"text":"but actually what language is, is speech. They are two things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":180885,"text":"Now of course, as history has gone by,"},{"time":184139,"text":"it's been natural for there to be a certain amount of bleed"},{"time":186930,"text":"between speech and writing."},{"time":189944,"text":"So, for example, in a distant era now,"},{"time":194767,"text":"it was common when one gave a speech"},{"time":197269,"text":"to basically talk like writing."},{"time":200386,"text":"So I mean the kind of speech that you see someone giving"},{"time":202736,"text":"in an old movie where they clear their throat, and they go,"},{"time":205269,"text":"\"Ahem, ladies and gentlemen,\" and then they speak"},{"time":207802,"text":"in a certain way which has nothing to do with casual speech."},{"time":211073,"text":"It's formal. It uses long sentences like this Gibbon one."},{"time":214932,"text":"It's basically talking like you write, and so, for example,"},{"time":218894,"text":"we're thinking so much these days about Lincoln"},{"time":220889,"text":"because of the movie."},{"time":223100,"text":"The Gettysburg Address was not the main meal of that event."},{"time":226183,"text":"For two hours before that, Edward Everett spoke"},{"time":230098,"text":"on a topic that, frankly, cannot engage us today"},{"time":233338,"text":"and barely did then."},{"time":234835,"text":"The point of it was to listen to him"},{"time":237216,"text":"speaking like writing."},{"time":238772,"text":"Ordinary people stood and listened to that for two hours."},{"time":241120,"text":"It was perfectly natural."},{"time":242553,"text":"That's what people did then, speaking like writing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":245044,"text":"Well, if you can speak like writing,"},{"time":247510,"text":"then logically it follows that you might want to also"},{"time":251308,"text":"sometimes write like you speak."},{"time":254174,"text":"The problem was just that in the material,"},{"time":256224,"text":"mechanical sense, that was harder back in the day"},{"time":259679,"text":"for the simple reason that materials don't lend themselves to it."},{"time":262986,"text":"It's almost impossible to do that with your hand"},{"time":265006,"text":"except in shorthand, and then communication is limited."},{"time":268441,"text":"On a manual typewriter it was very difficult,"},{"time":270957,"text":"and even when we had electric typewriters,"},{"time":273244,"text":"or then computer keyboards, the fact is"},{"time":275403,"text":"that even if you can type easily enough to keep up"},{"time":277702,"text":"with the pace of speech, more or less, you have to have"},{"time":280495,"text":"somebody who can receive your message quickly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":282840,"text":"Once you have things in your pocket that can receive that message,"},{"time":286051,"text":"then you have the conditions that allow"},{"time":288655,"text":"that we can write like we speak."},{"time":292166,"text":"And that's where texting comes in."},{"time":295384,"text":"And so, texting is very loose in its structure."},{"time":299153,"text":"No one thinks about capital letters or punctuation when one texts,"},{"time":303450,"text":"but then again, do you think about those things when you talk?"},{"time":305808,"text":"No, and so therefore why would you when you were texting?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":309481,"text":"What texting is, despite the fact that it involves"},{"time":312610,"text":"the brute mechanics of something that we call writing,"},{"time":315436,"text":"is fingered speech. That's what texting is."},{"time":318734,"text":"Now we can write the way we talk."},{"time":322199,"text":"And it's a very interesting thing, but nevertheless"},{"time":324978,"text":"easy to think that still it represents some sort of decline."},{"time":329834,"text":"We see this general bagginess of the structure,"},{"time":333118,"text":"the lack of concern with rules and the way that we're used to"},{"time":336467,"text":"learning on the blackboard, and so we think"},{"time":338739,"text":"that something has gone wrong."},{"time":341978,"text":"It's a very natural sense."}]},{"cues":[{"time":344941,"text":"But the fact of the matter is that what is going on"},{"time":348975,"text":"is a kind of emergent complexity."},{"time":352546,"text":"That's what we're seeing in this fingered speech."},{"time":355302,"text":"And in order to understand it, what we want to see"},{"time":358288,"text":"is the way, in this new kind of language,"},{"time":363033,"text":"there is new structure coming up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":366609,"text":"And so, for example, there is in texting a convention,"},{"time":372332,"text":"which is LOL."},{"time":375254,"text":"Now LOL, we generally think of"},{"time":377998,"text":"as meaning \"laughing out loud.\""},{"time":380462,"text":"And of course, theoretically, it does,"},{"time":382755,"text":"and if you look at older texts, then people used it"},{"time":385184,"text":"to actually indicate laughing out loud."},{"time":387704,"text":"But if you text now, or if you are someone who"},{"time":391947,"text":"is aware of the substrate of texting the way it's become,"},{"time":395244,"text":"you'll notice that LOL"},{"time":396934,"text":"does not mean laughing out loud anymore."},{"time":399004,"text":"It's evolved into something that is much subtler."}]},{"cues":[{"time":402794,"text":"This is an actual text that was done"},{"time":406241,"text":"by a non-male person of about 20 years old"},{"time":410173,"text":"not too long ago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":411668,"text":"\"I love the font you're using, btw.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":414620,"text":"Julie: \"lol thanks gmail is being slow right now\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":418382,"text":"Now if you think about it, that's not funny."},{"time":420124,"text":"No one's laughing. (Laughter)"},{"time":423024,"text":"And yet, there it is, so you assume"},{"time":424994,"text":"there's been some kind of hiccup."}]},{"cues":[{"time":426351,"text":"Then Susan says \"lol, I know,\""},{"time":428185,"text":"again more guffawing than we're used to"},{"time":430482,"text":"when you're talking about these inconveniences."}]},{"cues":[{"time":433712,"text":"So Julie says, \"I just sent you an email.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":436456,"text":"Susan: \"lol, I see it.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":438007,"text":"Very funny people, if that's what LOL means."}]},{"cues":[{"time":441625,"text":"This Julie says, \"So what's up?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":443753,"text":"Susan: \"lol, I have to write a 10 page paper.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":446395,"text":"She's not amused. Let's think about it."},{"time":448709,"text":"LOL is being used in a very particular way."},{"time":451390,"text":"It's a marker of empathy. It's a marker of accommodation."},{"time":455081,"text":"We linguists call things like that pragmatic particles."},{"time":458330,"text":"Any spoken language that's used by real people has them."},{"time":462169,"text":"If you happen to speak Japanese, think about"},{"time":463945,"text":"that little word \"ne\" that you use at the end of a lot of sentences."},{"time":467303,"text":"If you listen to the way black youth today speak,"},{"time":469648,"text":"think about the use of the word \"yo.\""},{"time":471434,"text":"Whole dissertations could be written about it,"},{"time":473380,"text":"and probably are being written about it."},{"time":475654,"text":"A pragmatic particle, that's what LOL has gradually become."},{"time":479448,"text":"It's a way of using the language between actual people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":483497,"text":"Another example is \"slash.\""},{"time":486736,"text":"Now, we can use slash in the way that we're used to,"},{"time":489504,"text":"along the lines of, \"We're going to have"},{"time":491144,"text":"a party-slash-networking session.\""},{"time":494626,"text":"That's kind of like what we're at."},{"time":496720,"text":"Slash is used in a very different way"},{"time":500259,"text":"in texting among young people today."},{"time":503217,"text":"It's used to change the scene."}]},{"cues":[{"time":505070,"text":"So for example, this Sally person says,"},{"time":508019,"text":"\"So I need to find people to chill with\""},{"time":509824,"text":"and Jake says, \"Haha\" --"},{"time":511343,"text":"you could write a dissertation about \"Haha\" too, but we don't have time for that —"},{"time":514231,"text":"\"Haha so you're going by yourself? Why?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":516720,"text":"Sally: \"For this summer program at NYU.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":519330,"text":"Jake: \"Haha. Slash I'm watching this video with suns players"},{"time":522224,"text":"trying to shoot with one eye.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":524021,"text":"The slash is interesting."},{"time":525296,"text":"I don't really even know what Jake is talking about after that,"},{"time":528452,"text":"but you notice that he's changing the topic."},{"time":533193,"text":"Now that seems kind of mundane,"},{"time":535011,"text":"but think about how in real life,"},{"time":536453,"text":"if we're having a conversation and we want to change the topic,"},{"time":539111,"text":"there are ways of doing it gracefully."},{"time":540723,"text":"You don't just zip right into it."},{"time":542442,"text":"You'll pat your thighs and look wistfully off into the distance,"},{"time":546637,"text":"or you'll say something like, \"Hmm, makes you think --\""},{"time":550747,"text":"when it really didn't, but what you're really --"},{"time":553107,"text":"(Laughter) —"},{"time":555342,"text":"what you're really trying to do is change the topic."},{"time":558050,"text":"You can't do that while you're texting,"},{"time":559977,"text":"and so ways are developing of doing it within this medium."},{"time":563708,"text":"All spoken languages have what a linguist calls"},{"time":565960,"text":"a new information marker -- or two, or three."},{"time":569353,"text":"Texting has developed one from this slash."}]},{"cues":[{"time":573647,"text":"So we have a whole battery of new constructions"},{"time":576632,"text":"that are developing, and yet it's easy to think,"},{"time":579219,"text":"well, something is still wrong."},{"time":581666,"text":"There's a lack of structure of some sort."},{"time":585441,"text":"It's not as sophisticated"},{"time":587347,"text":"as the language of The Wall Street Journal."},{"time":589553,"text":"Well, the fact of the matter is,"},{"time":591327,"text":"look at this person in 1956,"},{"time":593778,"text":"and this is when texting doesn't exist,"},{"time":596060,"text":"\"I Love Lucy\" is still on the air."}]},{"cues":[{"time":597895,"text":"\"Many do not know the alphabet or multiplication table,"},{"time":601658,"text":"cannot write grammatically -- \""}]},{"cues":[{"time":602995,"text":"We've heard that sort of thing before,"},{"time":605204,"text":"not just in 1956. 1917, Connecticut schoolteacher."},{"time":609195,"text":"1917. This is the time when we all assume"},{"time":611896,"text":"that everything somehow in terms of writing was perfect"},{"time":615147,"text":"because the people on \"Downton Abbey\" are articulate,"},{"time":617565,"text":"or something like that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":618776,"text":"So, \"From every college in the country goes up the cry,"},{"time":621720,"text":"'Our freshmen can't spell, can't punctuate.'\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":624353,"text":"And so on. You can go even further back than this."},{"time":626761,"text":"It's the President of Harvard. It's 1871."},{"time":629945,"text":"There's no electricity. People have three names."}]},{"cues":[{"time":632487,"text":"\"Bad spelling,"},{"time":634912,"text":"incorrectness as well as inelegance of expression in writing.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":638180,"text":"And he's talking about people who are otherwise"},{"time":640329,"text":"well prepared for college studies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":642220,"text":"You can go even further back."},{"time":644066,"text":"1841, some long-lost superintendent of schools is upset"},{"time":647919,"text":"because of what he has for a long time \"noted with regret"},{"time":651096,"text":"the almost entire neglect of the original\" blah blah blah blah blah."}]},{"cues":[{"time":654605,"text":"Or you can go all the way back to 63 A.D. -- (Laughter) --"},{"time":659893,"text":"and there's this poor man who doesn't like the way"},{"time":662274,"text":"people are speaking Latin."},{"time":663495,"text":"As it happens, he was writing about what had become French."},{"time":666651,"text":"And so, there are always — (Laughter) (Applause) —"},{"time":673053,"text":"there are always people worrying about these things"},{"time":675224,"text":"and the planet somehow seems to keep spinning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":678497,"text":"And so, the way I'm thinking of texting these days is"},{"time":683144,"text":"that what we're seeing is a whole new way of writing"},{"time":686724,"text":"that young people are developing,"},{"time":688350,"text":"which they're using alongside their ordinary writing skills,"},{"time":692110,"text":"and that means that they're able to do two things."},{"time":695277,"text":"Increasing evidence is that being bilingual"},{"time":698174,"text":"is cognitively beneficial."},{"time":700407,"text":"That's also true of being bidialectal."},{"time":702562,"text":"That's certainly true of being bidialectal in terms of your writing."},{"time":705652,"text":"And so texting actually is evidence of a balancing act"},{"time":710570,"text":"that young people are using today, not consciously, of course,"},{"time":713872,"text":"but it's an expansion of their linguistic repertoire."},{"time":717559,"text":"It's very simple."},{"time":718788,"text":"If somebody from 1973 looked at"},{"time":722498,"text":"what was on a dormitory message board in 1993,"},{"time":726604,"text":"the slang would have changed a little bit"},{"time":728437,"text":"since the era of \"Love Story,\""},{"time":730255,"text":"but they would understand what was on that message board."},{"time":733568,"text":"Take that person from 1993 -- not that long ago,"},{"time":736292,"text":"this is \"Bill and Ted's Excellent Adventure\" -- those people."},{"time":739550,"text":"Take those people and they read"},{"time":741919,"text":"a very typical text written by a 20-year-old today."},{"time":744819,"text":"Often they would have no idea what half of it meant"},{"time":747710,"text":"because a whole new language has developed"},{"time":751638,"text":"among our young people doing something as mundane"},{"time":753932,"text":"as what it looks like to us when they're batting around"},{"time":756203,"text":"on their little devices."}]},{"cues":[{"time":757878,"text":"So in closing, if I could go into the future,"},{"time":761539,"text":"if I could go into 2033,"},{"time":765914,"text":"the first thing I would ask is whether David Simon"},{"time":768827,"text":"had done a sequel to \"The Wire.\" I would want to know."},{"time":772720,"text":"And — I really would ask that —"},{"time":775703,"text":"and then I'd want to know actually what was going on on \"Downton Abbey.\""},{"time":778793,"text":"That'd be the second thing."},{"time":780302,"text":"And then the third thing would be,"},{"time":782838,"text":"please show me a sheaf of texts"},{"time":786029,"text":"written by 16-year-old girls,"},{"time":787986,"text":"because I would want to know where this language"},{"time":790440,"text":"had developed since our times,"},{"time":792395,"text":"and ideally I would then send them back to you and me now"},{"time":796028,"text":"so we could examine this linguistic miracle"},{"time":798548,"text":"happening right under our noses."},{"time":800898,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":802414,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":807582,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}